title: Jaspers Battle Hard but Lose 2-1 to St. John’s Red Storm
text:
Jaspers Battle Hard but Lose 2-1 to St. John’s Red Storm
The
Jaspers fell short against St. John's, losing 2-1 despite a strong effort. After a penalty kick by Macoumba Ba put St. John's ahead in the 21st minute, Ziv Dahan leveled the score with a header in the 55th minute. However, Miguel Diaz quickly restored St. John's lead just two minutes later, securing the victory. Both teams were eager to clinch their first win of the season, resulting in a physically demanding match. Manhattan's fatigue set in as they struggled to keep pace, despite a promising performance from returning players.
- Jaspers were outshot 9-6 by St. John's.
- Manhattan committed 19 fouls, while St. John's had 23.
- Manhattan's defense saw return of former MAAC Defender of the Year Nassim Akki.
- Junior goalkeeper Ludvig Malberg recorded two saves in goal.
Manhattan will take on #25 Seton Hall next, continuing their Big East schedule this Sunday. The Pirates are coming off a win against Albany and will pose another tough challenge for the Jaspers. The match will be streamed live at 1 p.m. on FloFC.Bottom Line
The Jaspers showed resilience but ultimately fell to St. John's. Key returnees provided a boost, though overcoming fatigue and tough competition remains critical moving forward. The upcoming match against Seton Hall will be pivotal for Manhattan's season prospects.

title: The Pope asks Zelensky to have the "courage" to "raise the white flag" and negotiate peace with Russia - World Today News
text:
ROMA, 9 Mar. (EUROPA PRESS) –
The Pope has urged the president of Ukraine, Volodymyr Zelensky, to have “courage” to raise the “white flag” and negotiate an end to the war with Russia .
«It is stronger that he sees the situation, that he thinks about the people, that he has the courage of the white flag, to negotiate. Today you can negotiate with the help of international powers. “The word negotiate is brave,” Francis said in an interview recorded last month with Swiss broadcaster RSI, ahead of Turkish President Tayyip Erdogan’s latest offer on Friday to host a summit between Ukraine and Russia to end the war.
«When you see that you are defeated, that things are not going well, you must have the courage to negotiate. You’re ashamed, but how many dead will it end up with? Negotiate on time, look for some countries that mediate. In the Ukrainian war, there are many. Türkiye has offered. And others. “Do not be ashamed to negotiate before it gets worse,” said the Pontiff in the interview with Swiss Radio and Television that will be broadcast on March 20 but of which some Italian media have already advanced fragments.
The Pope also answered a question about whether he had offered to negotiate in the conflicts in Ukraine and the Gaza Strip: “I am here, period. I have sent a letter to the Jews of Israel, asking them to reflect on this situation. Negotiating is never giving up. It is the value of not leading the country to suicide. The Ukrainians, with the history they have, poor things, the Ukrainians in Stalin’s time how much they suffered…
The Pope has denounced that behind wars “is the arms industry.”
“It is a collective sin,” he stated.
«A month ago, the treasurer told me how things were in the Vatican, always in deficit, do you know where the investments that give more income are today? The weapons factory. He earns by killing. More income: the weapons factory. “A terrible war,” he added.
Furthermore, he recalled that when he traveled to Redipuglia in 2014 he cried in front of the First World War memorial. » Then the same thing happened to me in Anzio, so every November 2nd I go to a cemetery to celebrate. Last time I went to the British cemetery and looked at the ages of the boys. I have already said it, but I will repeat it: “when the Normandy landings were commemorated, all the heads of Government celebrated that date, but no one said that up to 20,000 boys were left on that beach,” he said.
“War is crazy, it’s crazy,” he concluded.
Likewise, he has been asked about how the political leaders he receives at the Apostolic Palace respond when he asks for peace: “There are those who say, it’s true but you have to defend yourself… And then you realize that they have the airplane factory to bomb others. Defend ourselves, not destroy. How does a war end? With death, destruction, children without parents. There is always some geographical or historical situation that causes a war…. It may be a war that seems only for practical reasons. But behind a war is the arms industry, and that means money.
The Pope has also explained that every day at seven in the afternoon he calls the Argentine priest, Gabriel Romanelli, parish priest of the Holy Family of Gaza. «Six hundred people live there and tell what they see: it is a war. And war is waged by two, not one. The irresponsible ones are these two who wage war. Then there is not only military war, there is the “guerrilla war”, let’s say, of Hamas, a movement that is not an army. “It is something bad,” the Pope reflected.
In the same way, he has urged not to lose hope: “Let’s look at history, the wars we have experienced, they all end in agreement.”

author: Анастасия Фартыгина
title: Сербия и Россия договорились расширить программы обмена студентами
text:
Сербия и Россия договорились расширить программы обмена студентами
Министр образования Сербии Деян Станкович и министр просвещения России Сергей Кравцов встретились 11 июня на III Международном форуме министров образования «Формируя будущее» в Казани. На встрече обсуждалось расширение программ академического обмена между странам.
Сербия планирует активнее продвигать стипендии для своих студентов, чтобы они могли учиться в российских вузах в академическом 2025/2026 году.
— Наша цель — увеличить число школ, в которых цифровая компонента четко определена, и повысить уровень цифровых компетенций у учеников, преподавателей и директоров, — уточнил Станкович.
Министр подчеркнул важность интеграции искусственного интеллекта и цифровых технологий в образование. Он добавил, что эти аспекты уже отражены в стратегии развития ИИ в Сербии, а также в стратегии образования до 2030 года.
- Главная задача этих инициатив — подготовить молодежь к безопасному использованию современных технологий и пониманию роли искусственного интеллекта в обществе.
Форум «Формируя будущее» проходит 11-12 июня и предоставляет платформу для обсуждения актуальных вызовов в области образования, включая качество и доступность учебных программ.
Напомним, что на форуме помощник президента России Владимир Мединский рассказал подробнее о новых учебниках, а глава Минпросвещения страны Сергей Кравцов представил концепцию оценки системы образования. Подробнее — в репортаже «Реального времени».

author: Mary Carole McCauley
title: Three Baltimoreans awarded 2024 Guggenheim Fellowships
text: Three Baltimoreans — an author, an astrophysicist and a philosopher — [joined 185 other “midcareer culture creators”](https://www.gf.org/announcements/) Thursday in earning prestigious fellowships from the John Simon Guggenheim Memorial Foundation in New York. They are: [Sonia Shah](https://soniashah.com/), whose book topics span science, politics and human-animal relations; [Marc Kamionkowski](https://sites.krieger.jhu.edu/kamionkowski/), a professor at Johns Hopkins University who specializes in cosmology and particle physics; and [Jenann Ismael](https://www.jenanni.com/), the William H. Miller III Professor of Philosophy at Johns Hopkins University, where she explores questions about the structure of space and time and quantum mechanics. The Guggenheim Fellowship winners were winnowed from a pool of more than 3,000 applicants in 52 disciplines, according to a news release from the fellowship. Each Fellow will receive a grant to help support an independent project “at the highest level under the freest possible conditions.” Among the notable projects from prior years is Zora Neale Hurston’s 1936 book “Their Eyes Were Watching God.” Foundation president and poet Edward Hirsch said in the news release that the fellows are “generating new possibilities and pathways across the broader culture” in their work. The foundation has awarded over $400 million in fellowships to more than 19,000 mid-career innovators since its founding in 1925.

author: Dorothea Hecht
title: „Langsam wird's lästig": Seit Juli gibt's hier Probleme mit dem Internet
text:
Vodafone-Kunden betroffen
„Langsam wird's lästig“: Seit Juli gibt's hier Probleme mit dem Internet
Wehingen / Lesedauer: 2 min
Die Nachricht an unserer Redaktion schickt die Wehingerin aus dem öffentlichen WLAN bei Lidl. Von zuhause aus geht's nicht, und übers Handynetz auch nicht, denn mit dem Vodafone-Netz gibt es im Ort erhebliche Probleme. Seit 12. Juli dauere dieser Zustand nun schon an, beschwert sich Bettina Hussal: „Langsam wird's lästig!“
Auch bei der Wehinger Ortsverwaltung sind die Beschwerden aufgeschlagen. „Es gibt verschiedene Schadensfälle, die an Vodafone und auch schon an die Bundesnetzagentur gemeldet wurden“, sagt Hauptamtsleiter Konrad Häring. Welches Gebiet genau betroffen ist, kann er nicht sagen, da die Rückmeldung aus der Bevölkerung sehr unterschiedlich sei: „Bei manchen funktioniert's, bei manchen nicht.“
Häring hat versucht, über die Gemeinde bei Vodafone etwas zu erreichen. Doch eine Schadensursache habe ihm der Mobilfunk- und Internetanbieter bislang nicht genannt.
Vodafone hat auch selbst Probleme
Die Spurensuche verlaufe dabei äußerst schwierig, erzählt Häring. In einem Gespräch mit einer Vodafone-Mitarbeiterin habe diese selbst Leitungsprobleme bekommen. In einem anderen Fall wurde er an eine Mitarbeiterin verwiesen, deren Mailadresse nicht mehr aktiv war. „Es ist wirklich ärgerlich“, sagt er, „aber wir bleiben dran.“
Auf Anfrage unserer Redaktion nennt Vodafone selbst dann doch eine Ursache: Offenbar gibt es einen Schaden an der Stromzufuhr zu einem Mobilfunkmast der Deutschen Telekom AG, den Vodafone mit benutzt. Über Kooperationen wie diese sollen Funklöcher geschlossen werden.
Seit dem 11. Juli bestehe diese Störung, teilt die Pressestelle von Vodafone mit. Betroffen sei Wehingen und Umgebung, potenziell 1795 Kunden. Ganz so viele dürften es nicht sein, schon im benachbarten Gosheim sind keine Probleme bekannt. Einige Kilometer weiter in Bubsheim gab es zuletzt auch einen Ausfall bei Vodafone, der war nach einem Tag aber wieder behoben.
Fraglich, wann es besser wird
Wann der aktuelle Schaden in Wehingen behoben sein wird, kann Vodafone nicht sagen - die Telekom sei ja für den Mast zuständig. Eine Anfrage unserer Redaktion an die Telekom blieb bislang unbeantwortet.
Kurios wiederum: Telekom-Kunden haben offenbar keine Probleme mit ihrem Mobilfunk-Netz und der Internetverbindung - im Rathaus zum Beispiel läuft sie reibungslos.

author: Jane Harper
title: Virginia Beach Republican Party chairwoman indicted on felony charge
text: VIRGINIA BEACH — The chairwoman of the Republican Party of Virginia Beach was indicted this week on a felony charge of intercepting wire communications. Laura K. Hughes, an attorney and former Virginia Beach School Board member, was indicted Monday by a Virginia Beach grand jury, according to online court records. The crime carries a maximum penalty of five years in prison. Northampton County Commonwealth’s Attorney Jack Thornton on Thursday confirmed that his office was asked to handle the case after Virginia Beach Commonwealth’s Attorney Colin Stolle recused himself. Stolle is a longtime member of the local Republican Party. Thornton said he will personally prosecute the case, but declined to provide any other information. He said he has not yet seen the returned indictment. A spokeswoman for the Virginia Beach Commonwealth’s Attorney’s Office said she could not discuss the case. Hughes was recently chosen to lead the Republican Party of Virginia Beach, according to the [organization’s website,](https://rpvb.org/) which lists her term of service as being from 2024-26. She served as a member of the Virginia Beach School Board from 2018-22. The Pilot was unable to immediately reach Hughes for comment on Thursday. The [state law](https://law.lis.virginia.gov/vacode/title19.2/chapter6/section19.2-62/) under which she was charged states it is illegal for any person who is not a party to a communication to intentionally intercept, disclose, or use that communication without the consent of at least one involved party. The law also states that it’s illegal to use any wired or wireless device to intercept such a communication. The offense Hughes is accused of committing is alleged to have occurred in February. Jane Harper, jane.harper@pilotonline.com
